# Turkish İ/I Casing in English Words

HTML `lang="tr"` + CSS `text-transform: uppercase` causes browsers to convert `i` → `İ` (Turkish dotted capital I) instead of `I`.

## Rules

1. **English text with `text-transform: uppercase`**: Add `lang="en"` attribute to the element.
2. **Hardcoded uppercase English text** (e.g. marquee tickers): Write directly in uppercase in JSX — do not rely on CSS `text-transform`.
3. **Mixed Turkish/English content**: Wrap the English portion in a `<span lang="en">`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — "The Honey Scientist" becomes "THE HONEY SCİENTİST"
<span className={styles.logoSub}>The Honey Scientist</span>

// ✅ GOOD
<span className={styles.logoSub} lang="en">The Honey Scientist</span>
```
